item.title: Felipe Massa Crash in hungary qualifying
item.description:
Felipe Massa Crash in hungary qualifying
http://img.mtv3.fi/mn_kuvat/mtv3/etusivu/2009/07/755338.jpg Felipe Massa crashed heavily during the second part of qualifying for the Hungarian Grand Prix after apparently being struck by a piece of debris. The Ferrari driver went straight on at turn four of the Hungaroring. Replays suggested his crash helmet was hit by a piece of debris before he lost control. The accident comes just six days after Formula Two racer Henry Surtees was killed after his helmet was struck by a stray tyre. The start of the final part of qualifying was delayed by 20 minutes following the crash and teams of marshals sent around the circuit looking for further debris. Brawn confirmed that Rubens Barrichellos car had lost parts from its rear suspension. Barrichello went to visit his countryman at the circuit medical centre. Massa has been taken to hospital but his injuries are not though to be serious. http://bit.ly/1mNvHV https://paydotcom.com/sell.php?id=87259

item.title: Horror-Unfall von Massa! Gegenstand trifft ihn am Kopf
item.description:
Horror-Unfall von Massa! Gegenstand trifft ihn am Kopf
http://gameintrailer.com/kostenlose-ps3-xbox360-wii-bekommen/ Horror-Unfall von Felipe Massa beim Qualifying zum Großen Preis von Ungarn! Der Ferrari-Pilot raste schnurgerade und ohne Lenkbewegung aus einer Kurve, bohrte sich mit voller Wucht in einen Reifenstapel. Unglaublich: Ein herumfliegender Gegenstand hatte den Brasilianer voll am Kopf getroffen! Massa war schwer benommen, konnte nicht ohne Hilfe aus seinem Auto aussteigen. Rettungskräfte brachten ihn ins Medical Center an der Strecke, anschließend wurde der Brasilianer ins Krankenhaus gebracht. Laut einer ersten Mitteilung der FIA ist sein Zustand stabil. Erste Vermutung: Ein abgebrochenes Teil der Radaufhängung von Rubens Barrichello (Brawn) traf Massa am Helm. Der schien bewusstlos zu sein, bremste seinen Wagen aber noch ab. Trotzdem schlug Massa voll in die Reifenstapel ein. Barrichello war vor Massa auf der Strecke gefahren. Spekuliert wurde, dass der Gegenstand sogar Massas Visier durchschlug. Ein Fahrer berichtete, Massa habe eine Schnittwunde erlitten. Mercedes-Sportchef Norbert Haug: „Ich bin geschockt. Er ist innen über das Gras und dann voll in die Mauer gefahren. Er ist wohl von einem Metallteil am Kopf getroffen worden. Das kann man sich eigentlich gar nicht vorstellen. Es soll von Barrichello gewesen sein. Das ist schrecklich, furchtbar. Sollte Massa am Sonntag (14 Uhr) nicht starten können, darf Ferrari keinen Ersatzfahrer stellen. Ein Fahrerwechsel ist nur vor dem Qualifying erlaubt. Der Gewinner des Qualifyings war lange unklar, die Zeitnahme fiel aus. Stand nach einigen Minuten Chaos: Pole für Renault-Mann Fernando Alonso, Startplatz zwei für Sebastian Vettel. Sein Team-Kollege Mark Webber wurde Dritter. Gut für Vettel: WM-Spitzenreiter Jenson Button (Brawn) steht nur auf Platz 8. Bitter lief der Tag für die BMW-Piloten: Nick Heidfeld (als 16.) und Robert Kubica schieden schon im ersten Durchgang (Q1) aus. Auch für Adrian Sutil gab's im Force India das frühe Aus. Nachdem er im Vormittagstraining in einen Reifenstapel eingeschlagen war, wurde er nur 18.

item.title: Felipe Massa Terribile Incidente Ungheria 2009
item.description:
Felipe Massa Terribile Incidente Ungheria 2009
Il pilota della Ferrari Felipe Massa ha avuto un violento incidente durante le prove di qualificazione del Gp di Ungheria. Secondo fonti di Maranello Massa non ha subito ferite gravi. "Felipe è cosciente, ma ora sta andando all'ospedale di Budapest per accertamenti", spiega Luca Colajanni, della Ferrari. L'ipotesi è che si sia staccata una molla dalla Brawn Gp di Rubens Barrichello, che precedeva la Ferrari, e che ha colpito il casco di Massa sulla visiera, facendogli perdere i sensi. Da quel momento Massa non ha più reagito e la Ferrari è andata dritta senza più controllo contro le barriere. In quel punto la vettura del ferrarista procedeva a 280 km/h. Sul posto sono accorse due ambulanze, la safety-car e un elicottero. La vettura, che ha retto all'impatto con le barriere, è poi stata portata via dalla autogru. Il pilota brasiliano è stato condotto in ambulanza al centro medico e da lì in elicottero verso l'ospedale.

item.title: 3D Video (no glasses needed!) - Mosquito Highway
item.description:
3D Video (no glasses needed!) - Mosquito Highway
HOW TO VIEW IN 3D: Click on the "3D View Style" menu then select how you'd like to view. Red/Cyan are pretty common but see what works best for you. If you don't have glasses, then select "cross eyed" and just cross you eyes slightly to make the 2 videos overlap into 1. This is normally how I view 3D videos without glasses but if you're not able to overlap images with your eyes then you may want to just purchase a cheap pair of glasses somewhere online or buy a 3D movie from the store and use those glasses. Don't forget to click the full screen button on the bottom right of the video player as well... it helps if you have glasses. Sorry, Disney's fancy RealD polarized glasses don't work on these. PLEASE KEEP IN MIND... : This video was only a test for me to see how YouTube would handle it's new 3D feature. If this becomes popular and people are able to view it then I'll put more effort into the next one. I'd love to do this in my usual video quality. IF THIS DOESN'T WORK FOR YOU: - Cross-eyed can be difficult if you don't have control over your eye muscles. Try sitting away from the screen a bit or just get some practice in. There are a lot of cool videos like this on the net. - If you're using glasses and the image seems to be inside out then use your glasses the other way around. Some glasses are backwards. If your glasses can seperate the 2 images then it may be your computer monitor. A burned out, dull or discolored monitor may not work with your glasses. -STILL doesn't work with your glasses? Make sure you're using anaglyph glasses and not polarized glasses (like Disney RealD). YouTube doesn't support polarized. HOW DID I MAKE THIS? I simply used 2 identical (very cheap) cameras and placed them in the same general direction (both level with the lenses separated about 2 1/2 inches from each other). Then I resized the videos in editing and placed them next to each other (like you see in the "cross-eyed" setting). Once it was uploaded I added a few tags to trigger YouTube's new 3D viewing feature. The tag "yt3d:enable=true yt3d:aspect=3.55:4" is a custom tag I made specifically for this video and may not work for your video if you use it but it wouldn't hurt to try I guess. So just put that code into your tags if your video looks like mine. HOW TO ANIMATE IN 3D: Unfortunately, I had to cross my eyes to edit in 3D. I don't have any big fancy programs or a team to animate for me like most 3D studios have. So I like to keep it simple. It was a pain in the arse making this but it worked and I'm happy for that. YOUTUBE THE MOVIE!!!: If you happen to be in the LA area this Monday, July 27th you should totally check this out! - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TvyLWl7LOJI
